<subSubSection id="30DBC612538D384277B657B2C5AA1489" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="32522CF7E3EA85D7E8035D78FAF63E3B" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34A880296D43FD37854836303E46E0DD" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Males of 
<taxonomicName id="048F31257FE365C98C169052B4195020" genus="S." lsidName="S. canalae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="4F6CF053500B576200ED6E992AD2F8CA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb nov. shares with 
<taxonomicName id="F55F044020930D9AD280D79ABACCE4DB" genus="S." lsidName="S. tartara" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="tartara">
<emphasis id="CAE55A7F60B755606875816B0AD507A8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. tartara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. two patellar setae on the pedipalp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="895FD814DD788463DB60E45EFBDC0589" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T 75922) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">12C, D</figureCitation>
vs. Fig. 
<figureCitation id="9B19BC90128DAE239E53C3BCCEB78994" captionStart="Figure 22" captionStartId="F22" captionText="Figure 22. Salsa tartara sp. nov., male holotype (AM KS. 70737) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure22" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686621" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">22C, D</figureCitation>
). However, 
<taxonomicName id="AD9A776D493B88764E4DABA2D19F1512" genus="S." lsidName="S. canalae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="99E58C7292D9B44547C1EE9B65235640" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb nov. is distinguished by prominent, heavily sclerotised conductor of 
<taxonomicName id="447DE2FC12D3D6C96A9F733D2FDA915F" genus="S." lsidName="S. tartara" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="tartara">
<emphasis id="AF363933B8EFD2B76F32B172A4DD6F63" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. tartara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. which is short and inconspicuous in 
<taxonomicName id="FDE6E59B56CDEE7B9D34ADC639C06173" genus="S." lsidName="S. canalae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="D248F8B7669DBDEA94FC465932D81DB6" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. Female genitalia are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName id="A83315282CE5A77697CDB417974C0579" genus="S." lsidName="S. brisbanae" order="Araneida" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" rank="species" species="brisbanae">
<emphasis id="0FC09B601F5619C7D9335C3856DA3D1D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">S. brisbanae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov., but differ from those and other 
<taxonomicName id="BD646316E9B4C3B61F2037BEBA27A923" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A3BFD9C0369D3315E6CF0578C36408C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. species by the epigyne scape, that is longer than the epigyne plate and exceeds its posterior margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="45090C55714F4DB1B460E134D0D225D0" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13C, D</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A85A3A8E2413C3B9CFCACB18E060A17C" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="redescription">
<paragraph id="A6D60E9F29F839D2902DE6441395544B" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Redescription.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D4CD8DDFC7E3BAEBC69D7C562166144" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="1E2B9889586A663806A61C36CD843C6A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Male</emphasis>
(based on WAM T75922) Total length 5.5. Carapace 2.9 long, 2.5 wide, pear-shaped and pale brown, covered with short white setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8919D996A47DFFFAFE34B0B8B2C86D26" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T 75922) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">12A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.20, ALE 0.18, PME 0.13, PLE 0.11; row of eyes: AME 0.54, PME 0.47, PLE 1.22. Chelicerae yellowish brown; with four promarginal teeth (second basal largest) and three retromarginal teeth (basal largest). Legs yellowish brown mottled in pale brown, bearing thick setae on patella, tibia and metatarsus (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="65FC97F84AE1E8791A9F1D87875D1499" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T 75922) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">12A, B</figureCitation>
). Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 2.8 + 1.2 + 2.2 + 1.7 + 0.9 = 8.8, II - 2.2 + 1.0 + 1.6 + 1.6 + 0.8 = 7.2, III - 1.4 + 0.6 + 0.8 + 0.8 + 0.5 = 4.1, IV - 2.1 + 0.9 + 1.5 + 1.5 + 0.7 = 6.7. Labium 0.31 long, 0.47, and endites yellowish brown, paler anteriorly (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C54FF0A92EA5EF0DB351BB6436838E89" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T 75922) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">12B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.3 long, 0.8 wide, yellowish brown mottled dark and bearing dark brown contour (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="249B7CCB85D16FFA085D2581257CF5C2" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T 75922) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">12B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 2.5 long, 1.8 wide, with pointed conical posterior portion after spinnerets, dorsum, sides, and venter beige mottled in grey (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="BB6A8FA927D36CC1BA51A9B6E151CF0D" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T 75922) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">12A, B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="22193482CF5832F4302131099BB5A021" captionStart="Figure 12" captionStartId="F12" captionText="Figure 12. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T 75922) A dorsal habitus B ventral habitus C left pedipalp, ventral view D left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C, D)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">12C, D</figureCitation>
) length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + cymbium = total length): 0.5 + 0.2 + 0.15 + 0.9 = 1.75; patella with two setae; paracymbium reduced and straight; median apophysis elongated, with a thick basal process, a notched apical section on an acute and apically curved rounded tip; conductor lobe small; terminal apophysis subrectangular, apically projected and inflated, bearing a finger-like lobe from its basis; conductor flat with sclerotised borders; embolus short and strong, very sclerotised.
</paragraph>
<caption id="163AA7F42E56570FFD853DB99C2E51F1" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure12" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686611" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" start="Figure 12" startId="F12">
<paragraph id="6959B54FE5D60B0E73888AECE7F5C22F" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="3C21FB940C44FEDCC5B4FF335617B94D" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Figure 12.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="3D8C8D423C90B1FBE300C6FECEEA430E" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2022" baseAuthorityName="Berland" baseAuthorityYear="1924" class="Liliopsida" family="Araneidae" genus="Salsa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Salsa canalae" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="canalae">
<emphasis id="1AFB43FB324B06ACA8B9C03FE628F107" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Salsa canalae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Berland, 1924, comb. nov., male (WAM T75922) 
<emphasis id="80B446B0A5F7C9A71C249DE935855A22" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A</emphasis>
dorsal habitus 
<emphasis id="B307B03A6C7F05C5C8FFDAFD7824CFBF" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">B</emphasis>
ventral habitus 
<emphasis id="CBA9F7C1C3FF0DCE0C0118BF23570897" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C</emphasis>
left pedipalp, ventral view 
<emphasis id="14DFAAAD1596504B64AD8C9920B9109A" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">D</emphasis>
left pedipalp, dorsal view. Scale bars: 2 mm (
<emphasis id="B055D4B24031B20FF02DC861F8C6949B" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">A, B</emphasis>
); 0.2 mm (
<emphasis id="21DC12A479FE2DC68DB90DA43ED1FE7F" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">C, D</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="78085892391EB7E907C34894D0BC350A" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
<emphasis id="3ACBA7D3E753400673D1C85CE0BF265C" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Female</emphasis>
(based on WAM T75921): Total length 8.3. Carapace 3.5 long, 3.1 wide; dark brown and bearing long white setae throughout (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="55A4160313B006AE9C0CF2EC62FA4691" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13A</figureCitation>
). Eye diameter AME 0.20, ALE 0.18, PME 0.14, PLE 0.13; row of eyes: AME 0.52, PME 0.45, PLE 1.88. Chelicerae dark brown, four promarginal teeth (apical and basal largest), and three retromarginal (basal largest). Legs orange-brown, slightly darker on femur and joints (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A80EF2176CA76587CEE9229643BA3613" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13A, B</figureCitation>
). Pedipalp length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + tarsus = total length): 1.0 + 0.5 + 0.7 +1.1 = 3.3. Leg formula I&gt; II&gt; IV&gt; III; length of segments (femur + patella + tibia + metatarsus + tarsus = total length): I - 3.2 + 1.4 + 2.7 + 2.4 + 1.1 = 10.8, II - 2.8 + 1.5 + 2.2 + 2.2 + 0.9 = 9.6, III - 1.9 + 0.9 + 1.0 + 1.0 + 0.7 = 5.5, IV - 2.8 + 1.2 + 2.0 + 2.1 + 0.9 = 9.0. Labium 0.54 long, 0.86 wide and endites dark brown, beige on anterior border (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C42989050BE9953FE2869407BE8DD58E" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13B</figureCitation>
). Sternum 1.5 long, 1.5 wide and brown (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A8DA07A684F7F366928ACB7649A827A2" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13B</figureCitation>
). Abdomen 5.5 long, 5.2 wide; dorsum with beige background brindled in olive-grey (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F1DF3BCDB659C876A0B7200CCC3382BB" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13A</figureCitation>
); sides olive-grey (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0D8882C494DB947B496E2CF04168BFA7" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13B</figureCitation>
); venter olive-grey with two thick rounded white patches (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8515079A07457732AED6BF687DBF43D3" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13B</figureCitation>
). Epigyne subquadrate with broadly rounded antero-lateral borders and wide atrium and basis (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="49F98FFE70695E91D6737A0886800052" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13C, D</figureCitation>
); scape almost twice the length of epigyne base, from a slightly wide base gradually narrowing a thin section (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="476C7A91B4864501B647CCD6CF67C10A" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13C-E</figureCitation>
); central division goblet-like, very wide anteriorly, ca. as wide as the epigyne base, and tapering basally (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="2D153DE65E4BEEC997E212DCBD5171B1" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="F13" captionText="Figure 13. Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov., female A dorsal habitus (WAM T 75921) B ventral habitus (WAM T 75921) C epigyne, ventral view (WAM T 75921) D epigyne variation, ventral view (WAM T 75923) E epigyne variation, lateral view (WAM T 75923) F epigyne variation, posterior view (WAM T 75923). Scale bars: 2 mm (A, B); 0.2 mm (C-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure13" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686612" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">13F</figureCitation>
); spermathecae oval and apart by more than its diameter (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="84BFAB9F07144472C8EB9DA200095073" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Salsa gen. nov. female epigynes, cleared posterior view A S. fuliginata (L. Koch, 1872), comb. nov. (CVIC 173) B S. brisbanae (L. Koch, 1867), comb. nov. (AM KS. 131087) C S. canalae comb. nov. Berland, 1924, comb. nov. (WAM T 75921) D S. recherchensis (Main, 1954), comb. nov. (WAM T 77362) E S. rueda sp. nov. F S. tartara sp. nov. (AM KS. 7061). Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686604" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">5C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AA5477584D099E1C2A0B376AB0B2606B" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="variation">
<paragraph id="2A99055A7151120FAE492D3DA565D049" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Variation.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6262513A2F851F0646344223160373D3" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Only one male was available for measurements (see above); female total lengths 5.8 and 6.4 (
<emphasis id="F53FD0E87EFCD8F403800509814AE115" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">n</emphasis>
= 2). All our specimens were of very similar colouration, but 
<bibRefCitation id="D7D294CAB5B3154E7AD9E33ABCB53C6A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3853/j.0067-1975.18.1932.732" author="Berland, M" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Australian Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="295 - 299" refId="B3" refString="Berland, M, 1932. Araignees recueillies en Nouvelle-Caledonie par M. T. D. A. Cockerell. Records of the Australian Museum 18 (6): 295 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3853/j.0067-1975.18.1932.732" title="Araignees recueillies en Nouvelle-Caledonie par M. T. D. A. Cockerell." url="https://doi.org/10.3853/j.0067-1975.18.1932.732" volume="18" year="1932">Berland (1932)</bibRefCitation>
reported numerous females with considerable colour variations, specifically of the abdomen, without providing any further detail.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="375389EDF3E0F20E8B1DF96C3CB740C2" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="life history and habitat preferences">
<paragraph id="7CEEAF6AD67978FCBA4615BDEE499BBE" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Life history and habitat preferences.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0907447B2E330EFD49B1952E6DF2478E" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">The mature male described here was found in April, mature females examined between February and June; however, specimen numbers are too small to confidently interpret the phenology of the species. There was no information on habitat with any specimen labels.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="078D70F2DFCFD567FC7FC77003B726AD" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="EBE3AE0021AD219A4C4E4C128E8FC7DF" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B80C41840208B56E71826C68755AE312" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">
Distributed throughout New Caledonia (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="30237246804A712035CECDB5C66FD203" captionStart="Figure 14" captionStartId="F14" captionText="Figure 14. Distribution records of Salsa canalae Berland, 1924, comb. nov. in New Caledonia." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1102.82388.figure14" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/686613" pageId="0" pageNumber="107">14</figureCitation>
), including 
<normalizedToken id="016E0416518EF9149758DA4065BF6BF2" originalValue="Nouméa">Noumea</normalizedToken>
(cited in 
<bibRefCitation id="804EB7E88B58CDD800D6F770EA4201CF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3853/j.0067-1975.18.1932.732" author="Berland, M" journalOrPublisher="Records of the Australian Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="107" pagination="295 - 299" refId="B3" refString="Berland, M, 1932. Araignees recueillies en Nouvelle-Caledonie par M. T. D. A. Cockerell. Records of the Australian Museum 18 (6): 295 - 299, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3853/j.0067-1975.18.1932.732" title="Araignees recueillies en Nouvelle-Caledonie par M. T. D. A. Cockerell." url="https://doi.org/10.3853/j.0067-1975.18.1932.732" volume="18" year="1932">Berland 1932</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
